 	Pig script commands works as follows-
 	 
 	LOAD-
 	LOAD command is used to load the data from the file system (local/HDFS) into a relation.
 	b = load '/hadoopdata/pig/himanshu.txt' using PigStorage(',') as (b1:int, b2:int, b3:int);
 	 
 	STORE-
 	STORE command is used to save a relation to the file system (local/HDFS).
 	STORE 5 INTO '/pigoutput';
 	 
 	DUMP-
 	DUMP command is used to print the contents of a relation on the console.
 	Dump a ;
 	 
 	FOREACH-
 	FOREACH command is used to generate data transformations based on columns of data.
 	2 = FOREACH c GENERATE b1, b2, b2*b3;
 	 
 	FILTER-
 	FILTER command is used to remove unwanted rows from a relation.
 	f = FILTER a by $5 > 5;
 	 
 	GROUP BY- 
 	GROUP BY command is used to group the data in a single relation.
 	g = GROUP a by $1;
 	 
 	g = GROUP n by ($1,$2); 
 	 
 	m = GROUP c ALL;
 	 
 	ORDER BY- 
 	ORDER BY command is used to arrange a relation in a sorted order based on one or more fields (ascending or descending).
 	f = order c by b1 desc ;
 	 
 	DESCRIBE-
 	DESCRIBE command is used to describe the schema of a relation.
 	describe h;
